/**
 * @category Tests
 * @summary A call to an undeclared bare name is a static analyzer error on
 * BOTH paths (1.16.0), so the evaluator rejects it like the VM compiler
 * does, even when the call is wrapped in throw or try/catch.
 */
import io;
try {
    throw RangeError("not a built-in error class");
} catch (Error e) {
    io.println("never analyzed away");
}
